nmap -p-    = full port scan 
nmap -Pn    = Don't wait for host ping reply, persume host is up
nmap -sS    = stealthy scan only complete 2 parts of the handshake
nmap -sP    = ping only scan, returns no port just host status (Down / Up)
nmap -open  = Show only open ports
nmap -T4    = How fast you want to implement the scan, T4 is commony used , T5 is very noisy on a network.
nmap -n     = Do not resolve DNS (DNS resolution is time consuming, use if you don't need to know host name)
nmap -A     = O/S & Service Version Detection 
nmap -sC    = Use Safe Scripts
